Psephellus vanensis

is endemic to east Anatolia, where it seems to be very local. It belongs to the Irano-Turanian element (Fig. 
4
). The species is known only from type gatherings and from an area of approximately 0,006 km2 (criterion B1). Because of overgrazing, the habitat of this species is under threat, and this situation leads to potential reduction in the number of individuals (criterion A). The population is in a poor condition, and the number of individuals is estimated to approximately 120-125 (criterion C2). Therefore the species should be regarded as Critically Endangered (
IUCN 2014
).
